description:
Carpe Noctem is a horror story unlike anything that has come before.

A small time journalist, Chelsea Nobles is thrown into the tumultuous underworld of Las Vegas, Nevada. Imbued with the ancient powers of the “Scribe” she discovers that hidden amongst the bright lights, and high stakes hustle of the Vegas strip, is a dark and twisted reality that conceals some of fiction's most terrifying, and magnificent creatures. Now tasked with documenting the exploits of notorious Sin City entrepreneurs, Jace and Dante Rivera, owners of “Carpe Noctem” the most popular nightclub in the “Capital of Second Chances”.

The brothers, always at odds, are descended from an ancient vampire Goddess.

As Chelsea learns more about her extraordinary Scribe powers, Dante Rivera continues his reckless behavior and in the process infuriates the Goblin King, Isaac Bottwin who sends an army of Zombies to the Rivera brothers front door.

Carpe Noctem presents a dark new lore. for horror fans. This next step in the genre bending world of supernatural/horror has been brought to life by the creative minds of Martin Dunn and Derrick Fish.Together, they have redefined the mythos of monster stories.

Collected Editions

  • Carpe Noctem: Lost Vegas Vol. 1 (#1-3)
  • Carpe Noctem: Lost Vegas Vol. 2 (#4-6)
name: Carpe Noctem
